I went to the International Cafe today and ordered a chicken Phili without Mushrooms. Unfortunately the order was done incorrectly.  This wouldn't be so bad if it was the first time however this has happened to me more times than I care to count. As a matter of fact it's a running joke with my coworkers as to weather my order will be correct or not! I called and made them aware of the mistake and took the sandwich back just like in the past. Now what I have a big problem with is how the mistake is handled.  Yes the sandwich is remade but I had to make a second trip to you shop to fix an error that I had nothing to do with. I was offered nothing for my inconvenience!!! Drink, cookie, money back etc. They even kept the sandwich that was I correctly made. This saddens me because I work downtown and like the food but this last issue has truly turned me off to this restaurant.  I don't think i will be returning again.

You can pick a bag of chips for your side; its not a place you can choose better sides. Thats it. When we are in a rush or its late & we need to grab lunch downtown, we will go here but it's generally out of necessity as opposed to choice.

We go out of our way to support locally owned, small businesses and do want to "like" this restaurant, but it is hard to.  The food is very good and is priced fairly. The issue we have however is with the "casual" way the staff interacts together and as though their jobs are an afterthought. I have seen this happen all while a man is present who seems to be the owner or manager and himself has been very customer oriented so I do not understand why, if he is the owner or manager, he does not demand the same of his staff.  I do not like posting negative reviews however, there was an incident that is hard to ignore. A few weeks back we stopped in around 2 and I guess they were in closing mode. That is understandable, but what was inexcusable was that the cashier stated eating a sandwich then handling our order. This was not only gross but was likely a sanitation code violation. Our food was "to-go" and we tossed it out upon leaving and went to another restaurant for lunch.  We do not plan to return.
